Hi,

   First thanks a bunch for ddccontrol / gddccontrol, I use it a lot,
specially the profile capabilities. I have profiles for regular PC use,
TV-use (mythtv), photography (I calibrated my monitor).

   Now that I have my profiles well defined, I want to setup Desktop
shortcuts / scripts so that clicking an Icon, I could have gddccontrol load
a profile. For this, I need gddccontrol (or ddccontrol) to take a Profile
name as a command line option, and apply it, then exit.

   I explored a little bit ddccontrol & gddccontrol documentation, and it
looks like the functionality is not there. (BTW, gddccontrol has a funny
behaviour when invoked like this: gddccontrol --help)

   Is it possible for you guys to consider adding this feature in some
future release?

Thanks!!!!
Ari

